            "title": "Intro",
            "id": 126905,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Let's dive into controlling the times a while loop repeats its code, like this page that uses a loop to run its code from <code>1</code> to <code>10</code> times.</p><webview version=\"2\" content=\"&lt;!doctype html&gt;&#xA;&lt;html&gt;&#xA; &lt;head&gt;&#xA;  &lt;style&gt;&#xA;   body {&#xA;    min-height: 440px;&#xA;    text-align: center;&#xA;   }&#xA;   &#xA;   input {&#xA;    height: 25px;&#xA;   }&#xA;   &#xA;   em,&#xA;   h3,&#xA;   #slider {&#xA;    text-align: center;&#xA;   }&#xA;  &lt;/style&gt;&#xA; &lt;/head&gt;&#xA; &lt;body&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div style=&quot;display: inline-block; text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&#xA;   &lt;em&gt;Move the input element below&lt;/em&gt;&#xA;   &lt;h3&gt;Items per page: &lt;span id=&quot;itemsPerPage&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;   &lt;div id=&quot;slider&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 25px;&quot;&gt;1 &lt;input min=&quot;1&quot;&#xA;     max=&quot;10&quot; oninput=&quot;generateList(this.value);&quot; type=&quot;range&quot;&#xA;     value=&quot;3&quot;&gt; 10&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;   &lt;ol id=&quot;list&quot;&gt;&#xA;   &lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;script&gt;&#xA;   generateList(3);&#xA;   &#xA;   func generateList(_ itemCount: Int) {&#xA;    let itemsPerPage = document.getElementById(&quot;itemsPerPage&quot;);&#xA;    itemsPerPage.innerHTML = String(itemCount);&#xA;    let list = document.getElementById(&quot;list&quot;);&#xA;    list.innerHTML = &quot;&quot;;&#xA;    var counter = 1;&#xA;    while (counter &lt;= itemCount) {&#xA;     var item = document.createElement(&quot;li&quot;);&#xA;     item.innerHTML ='&lt;img src=&quot;https://mimo.app/i/camera.png&quot; height=25&gt; Camera';&#xA;     list.appendChild(item);&#xA;     counter+=1;&#xA;    }&#xA;   }&#xA;  &lt;/script&gt;&#xA; &lt;/body&gt;&#xA;&lt;/html&gt;\" /></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "While Loops",
            "id": 126906,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>To control the number of times a <code>while</code> loop repeats, we start with a variable set to a number. We call this variable a <strong>counter variable</strong>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"swift\" name=\"main.swift\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"var\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" counter = \" /><text value=\"1\" class=\"number\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"14\" endIndex=\"15\" /><option correct=\"false\"><content><text value=\"true\" /></content></option></options></interaction></interactions></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>1</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "While Loops",
            "id": 126907,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Then, we use a comparison in the condition to compare the counter variable to a number. In this case, <code>counter &lt; 4</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"swift\" name=\"main.swift\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"var\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" counter = \" /><text value=\"1\" class=\"number\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"while\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" counter &lt; \" /><text value=\"4\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\" {}\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"22\" endIndex=\"29\" /><option startIndex=\"30\" endIndex=\"31\" /><option startIndex=\"32\" endIndex=\"33\" /><option correct=\"false\"><content><text value=\"&gt;\" /></content></option></options></interaction></interactions></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>counter</code>, followed by <code>&lt;</code>, and finally <code>4</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "While Loops",
            "id": 126908,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Inside the code block, we make the condition return <code>false</code> and stop the loop by incrementing the counter variable. Try it with <code>counter += 1</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"swift\" name=\"main.swift\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"var\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" counter = \" /><text value=\"1\" class=\"number\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"while\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" counter &lt; \" /><text value=\"4\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\" {\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"print\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\"(counter)\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\" counter += \" /><text value=\"1\" class=\"number\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"}\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"validatedInput\" isDefault=\"true\" startIndex=\"53\" endIndex=\"65\" /></interactions><output><content><text value=\"1\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"2\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"3\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to type <code>counter += 1</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Changing the condition",
            "id": 126909,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Changing the condition tells the loop when to stop. For example, changing the condition to <code>counter &lt; 10</code>.</p><code name=\"main.swift\" version=\"2\" codelang=\"swift\"><content><text value=\"var\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" counter = \" /><text value=\"1\" class=\"number\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"while\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" counter &lt; \" /><text value=\"10\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\" {\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"print\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\"(counter)\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\" counter += \" /><text value=\"1\" class=\"number\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"}\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option correct=\"false\"><content><text value=\"4\" /></content></option><option startIndex=\"32\" endIndex=\"34\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"1\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"2\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"3\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"4\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"5\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"6\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"7\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"8\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"9\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>10</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Changing the counter variable",
            "id": 126910,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Changing the counter variable's value changes when the loop starts. Like setting <code>counter</code> to <code>5</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"swift\" name=\"main.swift\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"var\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" counter = \" /><text value=\"5\" class=\"number\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"while\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" counter &lt; \" /><text value=\"10\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\" {\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"print\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\"(counter)\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\" counter += \" /><text value=\"1\" class=\"number\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"}\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"validatedInput\" isDefault=\"true\" startIndex=\"14\" endIndex=\"15\" /></interactions><output><content><text value=\"5\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"6\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"7\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"8\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"9\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to type <code>5</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Code in the code block",
            "id": 126911,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Since the whole code block runs, the order you write code affects what the console displays. Place <code>counter += 1</code> first to display <code>6</code> through <code>10</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"swift\" name=\"main.swift\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"var\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" counter = \" /><text value=\"5\" class=\"number\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"while\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" counter &lt; \" /><text value=\"10\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\" {\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\" counter += \" /><text value=\"1\" class=\"number\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"print\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\"(counter)\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"}\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"38\" endIndex=\"50\" /><option startIndex=\"52\" endIndex=\"66\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"6\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"7\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"8\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"9\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"10\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>counter += 1</code>, followed by <code>print(counter)</code>.</p></body></html>"
